Package: hiddenmeta
Type: Package
Title: Meta-analysis of hidden population studies
Version: 0.1.2
Date: 2020-11-20
Author: 
    c(person(given = "Georgiy", family = "Syunyaev", email = "gs2716@columbia.edu",
             role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person(given = "Macartan", family = "Humphreys", email = "macartan@gmail.com",
             role = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Georgiy Syunyaev <gs2716@columbia.edu>
Description: Helper functions for analysis of individual and multiple studies of 
    hidden population size and prevalence using RDS, TLS or PPS designs. 
    The functions are written so that they can be used with DeclareDesign package to 
    allow for easy declaration of one or more studies with various design features. 
    In addition, package implements functions for estimation of hidden population size and prevalance based on 
    RDS, TLS or PPS samples.
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.0.0),
    magrittr (>= 2.0.0), 
    dplyr (>= 1.0.0)
